The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Corporate Briefs
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                   Corporate Briefs
                              
	 Bharti Retail will focus on Punjab and then move on to consolidate its position in northern India. Our focus right now is Punjab and we will first consolidate our presence in north India, Bharti Retail president and CEO Vinod Sawhney said. The company recently launched three food and grocery stores under the brand Easy Days in Ludhiana. The company will also focus on private labels at the stores. The company aims to invest $2.5 billion in multiple format stores by 2015.                             
	 Bharti Rashtriya Chemicals amp; Fertilizers (RCF) has posted a profit of Rs 51.37 crore for the fourth quarter ended March 31, 2008 against Rs 33.31 crore during the corresponding period of the previous fiscal. The total income rose to Rs 1,389.29 crore during the quarter against Rs 948.26 crore last year.                             
	 GN has launched seven models in the mobile segment. GN has also showcased a range of bluetooth headsets that will be introduced in India this year. This includes BT5010 and BT5020 in the medium-priced segment, BT8010 and BT8040 in premium , BT3030 in music and BT2010 and BT2020 in the entry-level segment.                             
	 Sunil Hitech Engineers Ltd has clocked a growth of 143 per cent in net sales at Rs 112.37 crore for the fourth quarter of 2007-08 compared with Rs 46.33 crore in the corresponding period of the previous fiscal. Profit after tax stood at Rs 7.30 crore, up 122 per cent, from Rs 3.28 crore in the corresponding quarter of the previous year.                             
	 GE Consumer amp; Industrial has bagged orders worth Rs 20 crore for the Commonwealth Games in 2010 and the Indian Premier League matches, to provide lighting solutions to the Jawaharlal Nehru stadium and the Ferozeshah Kotla stadium, respectively.                             
	 Suzuki Motorcycle India has upgraded two motorcycles, Zeus and Heat 125. The Suzuki Zeus 125 is available in three variants  Zeus XCD with self-start, disc and alloys, the second variant Zeus XEU comes with alloys and self start and the third variant Zeus XDU comes with self start and drum brakes.                             
	 Bharti Airtel Ltd has introduced the Airtel phone back-up service that enables customers to store and retrieve all kinds of phone data. The data that can be backed up and restored depends on the phone model.                             
	 Coffee Day Xpress has introduced multi-cuisine menus in all its 45 kiosks in Calcutta. With prices starting from Rs 15 onwards, Coffee Day Xpress serves a variety of fresh and hygienic food and beverages.                                                                                                                  ADVERTISEMENT                   
